<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62ddc710-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s5209"><num value="5209">§ 5209.</num><heading> Rules and regulations; repeals</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of the Interior is authorized to prescribe such rules and regulations as may be necessary to carry out the provisions of this chapter. All Acts or parts of Acts inconsistent with this chapter are repealed.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id62ddc711-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1936-06-26/ch831/s9">June 26, 1936, ch. 831, § 9</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/49/1968">49 Stat. 1968</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id62ddc712-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id62ddc713-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id62ddc714-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t25/s509">section 509 of this title</ref> prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
